headline: Amphenol Gets an Upgrade. There’s More to the Story Than AI Data Centers.
summary: Shares of  Amphenol  the maker of fiber-optic cables and connectors, have surged 81% this year.  BofA  Securities upgraded Amphenol to Buy from Neutral on Wednesday, raising its target for the stock price to $150 from $120.  Artificial intelligence is “driving interconnect demand even higher,” the bank said.

headline: Abbott narrows outlook, Australian stocks react to US-China trade
summary: Yahoo Finance host Josh Lipton tracks today's top moving stocks and biggest market stories in this Market Minute, including Abbott Laboratories (ABT) shares slipping after the company narrowed its full-year guidance, Amphenol (APH) receiving an upgrade to Buy, and Australian stocks — like Australian Oilseeds (COOT) — are reacting to the rare earth trade tensions between the US and China. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.
